pacman::p_load(tidyverse, lubridate)

dat <- read_csv("../.Rdata/US Onions.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_character(),
##   Week = col_date(format = ""),
##   UPC = col_double(),
##   `GA $` = col_double(),
##   `GA EQ` = col_double(),
##   `GA $ Prior Yr` = col_double(),
##   `GA EQ Prior Yr` = col_double()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
dat <-  dat %>% 
  mutate(ppp = `GA $` /`GA EQ`, pppl = `GA $ Prior Yr` / `GA EQ Prior Yr`, date = ymd(Week)) %>% 
  filter(`BC SUB CATEGORY` != "VALUE ADD", ppp < 60, pppl < 50)
  

par(mfrow = c(1,2))
dat %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_jitter(aes(x = date, y = ppp, color = `BC SUB CATEGORY`), height = 0, width = .4, alpha = .5) +
  geom_smooth(aes(x = date, y = ppp, color = `BC SUB CATEGORY`), se = FALSE) +
  labs(y = "Price Per Pound", x = "Week")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'

dat %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_jitter(aes(x = date, y = pppl, color = `BC SUB CATEGORY`), height = 0, width = .4, alpha = .5) +
  geom_smooth(aes(x = date, y = pppl, color = `BC SUB CATEGORY`), se = FALSE) +
  labs(y = "Price Per Pound", x = "Week")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
